title: Australian Government - Wikipedia
snippet: The governor-general usually presides at council meetings, but in their absence another minister nominated as the vice-president of the Executive Council presides at the meeting of the council. Since 1 June 2022, the vice-president has been senator Katy Gallagher. As of 13 May 2025, there are 16 departments of the Australian Government.

title: Anthony Albanese - Wikipedia
snippet: He also administered the official commencement of the AUKUS security pact between Australia, the United States, and the United Kingdom, and navigated Australia's response to the Gaza war. Despite often scoring low approval ratings, his government was re-elected in a landslide victory in the 2025 election, resulting in one of the largest Labor governments in Australian history.
